{"data": [{"id": "4194287", "title": "GR Silver Mining CFO Blaine Bailey to retire", "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>GR Silver Mining (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GRSLF\" title=\"GR SILVER MNG LTD.\">OTCQB:GRSLF</a>) said its <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/19888550-gr-silver-mining-announces-change-in-cfo\">CFO\u00a0Blaine Bailey</a> will retire from the role, effective immediately.</li>\n<li>The firm said it has appointed\u00a0Robert Payment to the role of the finance chief.</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194287-gr-silver-mining-cfo-blaine-bailey-to-retire", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:53:22"}, {"id": "4194289", "title": "Boeing in charts: Commercial Airplanes deliveries surge 10.5% Y/Y in Q3, while revenues fall 5.5%", "description": "<html><body><div>\n<a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA1.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA1_thumb1.png\" width=\"100%\"/></a><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA3.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA3_thumb1.png\" width=\"100%\"/></a><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA4.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA4_thumb1.png\" width=\"100%\"/></a><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA2.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA2_thumb1.png\" width=\"100%\"/></a><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA5.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_BA5_thumb1.png\" width=\"100%\"/></a>\n</div></body></html>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194289-boeing-in-charts-commercial-airplanes-deliveries-surge-105-yy-in-q3-while-revenues-fall-55", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:54:42"}, {"id": "4194284", "title": "Diversified Energy inks gas supply deal with Gulf Coast LNG facility", "description": "<html><body><p>Diversified Energy (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DEC\" title=\"Diversified Energy Company PLC\">OTCQX:DEC</a>) on Wednesday announced a multiyear <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/19888491-diversified-announces-natural-gas-supply-contract-major-gulf-coast-lng-facility\">supply agreement</a> with an unnamed \"major Gulf Coast LNG facility\" to provide natural gas to export.</p> <p>Under the deal terms, Diversified (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DEC\" title=\"Diversified Energy Company PLC\">OTCQX:DEC</a>) will provide ~40B cf of natural gas for three years<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> starting in November under a fixed pricing construct indexed to Gulf Coast pricing.</span></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The company also said it has taken advantage of the recent strength of the natural gas price curve to add to its hedge portfolio in 2025-27, with an average Nymex hedge price of ~$3.45/MMBtu.</p> </body></html>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518095448/image_518095448.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194284-diversified-energy-inks-gas-supply-deal-with-gulf-coast-lng-facility", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:47:23"}, {"id": "4194239", "title": "Earnings Snapshot: Coca-Cola tops Q3 profit, revenue estimates", "description": "<html><body><div><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_KO_1.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_KO_1_thumb1.png\" width=\"100%\"/></a></div>\n<div><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_KO_2.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/23/saupload_KO_2_thumb1.png\" width=\"100%\"/></a></div></body></html>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194239-earnings-snapshot-coca-cola-tops-q3-profit-revenue-estimates", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:44:08"}, {"id": "4194119", "title": "Microsoft co-founder Gates donated $50M to Harris to win election: report", "description": "<html><body><p>Microsoft (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MSFT\" title=\"Microsoft Corporation\">MSFT</a></span>) co-founder Bill Gates has said privately that he has donated $50M to a nonprofit organization that is supporting Vice President Kamala Harris to win the 2024 U.S. presidential election, The New York Times reported.</p> <p>The donation was supposed to<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> be kept under wraps and was made to the Future Forward organization, which has become the main fundraising organization outside the official Harris campaign, the news outlet </span><a class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/22/us/elections/bill-gates-future-forward-kamala-harris.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">added</a><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">, citing people briefed on the matter.</span></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The donation went to Future Forward's non-profit arm, which is a tax-exempt 501(c)(4) organization and does not have to disclose its donors, The Times added.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">While Gates has said he can work with either candidate, he has expressed concern what a second term for former President Trump would look like and is \"significantly concerned\" about potential cuts to family planning and global health programs if Trump were re-elected, some of the people added.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Gates is said to not have a \"deep relationship\" with Vice President Harris but has publicly congratulated the Biden administration for its work on climate change.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">In a statement to the Times, Gates did not acknowledge the donation, but said this election is different, with \"unprecedented significance.\"</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">\u201cI support candidates who demonstrate a clear commitment to improving health care, reducing poverty and fighting climate change in the U.S. and around the world,\u201d Gates told The New York Times. \u201cI have a long history of working with leaders across the political spectrum, but this election is different, with unprecedented significance for Americans and the most vulnerable people around the world.\u201d</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Gates was a member of the board of directors for Microsoft and Berkshire Hathaway (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BRK.A\" title=\"Berkshire Hathaway Inc.\">BRK.A</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BRK.B\" title=\"Berkshire Hathaway Inc.\">BRK.B</a>) until he stepped down in 2020 to focus on his philanthropic efforts at the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation. He stepped down from his role of CEO at Microsoft in 2000.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Microsoft did not immediately respond to a request for comment from Seeking Alpha.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Readers interested in investing topics tied to the upcoming election can find more information at the upcoming <strong>Seeking Alpha Investing Forum: Election 2024;</strong> please visit the <a href=\"https://subscriptions.seekingalpha.com/events_election_event_2024/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">event website</a>.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"><strong>Dear readers:</strong> We recognize that politics often intersects with the financial news of the day, so we invite you to click <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4726497-politics-and-the-markets-102324\">here</a> to join the separate political discussion.</p> </body></html>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2178405094/image_2178405094.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194119-microsoft-co-founder-gates-donated-50m-to-harris-to-win-election-report", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:44:16"}, {"id": "4194203", "title": "Watsco misses Q3 estimates", "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Watsco <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/19888542-watsco-reports-record-sales-enhanced-operating-efficiency-strong-cash-flow-and-improving\" target=\"_blank\">press release</a>  (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WSO\" title=\"Watsco, Inc.\">WSO</a></span>): Q3  GAAP EPS of $4.22 <font color=\"red\"> misses by $0.52</font>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $2.16B <font color=\"red\"> misses by $80M</font>.</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194203-watsco-misses-q3-estimates", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:37:51"}, {"id": "4194204", "title": "Winnebago slides after earnings reflect sluggish retail demand", "description": "<html><body><p>Winnebago Industries (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WGO\" title=\"Winnebago Industries, Inc.\">WGO</a></span>) reported a 6.5% decline in revenue in FQ4 to $720.9 million. The revenue decrease reflected the sluggish retail demand environment and operating inefficiencies within the Winnebago branded businesses. Revenue in the towable RV segment was down 7.2%, while revenue in the<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> motorhome RV segment was down 3.1%.</span></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">CEO Michael Happe said the RV industry continues to face various headwinds, including uncertain retail conditions, higher inventory carrying costs and slightly elevated inventories in the motorhome segment, leading to continued dealer hesitancy and increased promotional efforts. \"Despite the challenging operating conditions, in the fourth quarter we continued to focus on the variables within our control. We prioritized profitability and cash generation, aggressively managed inventory, and invested in new products and technologies to drive future growth,\" he highlighted.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Gross profit margin decreased 340 basis points during the quarter to 13.1%, reflecting higher warranty expense, operational challenges, and deleverage. Winnebago (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WGO\" title=\"Winnebago Industries, Inc.\">WGO</a>) saw an operating loss of $17.8 million vs. operating income of $57.5 million in FQ4 last year. Consolidate adjusted EBITDA was down 60% year-over-year to $28.7 million, vs. $48.9 million consensus. EPS came in at $0.28 vs. $1.41 a year ago.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Looking ahead, Winnebago Industries (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WGO\" title=\"Winnebago Industries, Inc.\">WGO</a>) anticipates total North American RV wholesale shipments in the range of 320,000 to 350,000 units. Based on that outlook and the current business environment, the company expects FY25 consolidated revenues in the range of $2.9 billion to $3.2 billion, reported earnings per diluted share of $2.40 to $3.90, and adjusted earnings per diluted share of $3.00 to $4.50. WGO's outlook considers prevailing trends in the RV sector, including competitive dynamics, shifts in consumer preferences, and key macroeconomic factors that may influence overall demand.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Shares of Winnebago (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WGO\" title=\"Winnebago Industries, Inc.\">WGO</a>) fell <span class=\"red\">7.78%</span> in premarket trading on Wednesday. Recreation vehicle stocks in general are mixed in the premarket session as well, including Lazydays Holdings (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GORV\" title=\"Lazydays Holdings, Inc.\">GORV</a>) <span class=\"green\">+2.2%</span>, Thor Industries (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/THO\" title=\"THOR Industries, Inc.\">THO</a>) <span class=\"red\">-2.4%</span>, LCI Industries (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LCII\" title=\"LCI Industries\">LCII</a>) <span class=\"red\">-0.2%</span>, Camping World (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CWH\" title=\"Camping World Holdings, Inc.\">CWH</a>) <span class=\"red\">-2.6%</span>, Malibu Boats (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MBUU\" title=\"Malibu Boats, Inc.\">MBUU</a>) <span class=\"green\">+0.1%</span>, MasterCraft Boat Holdings (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MCFT\" title=\"MasterCraft Boat Holdings, Inc.\">MCFT</a>) <span class=\"red\">-0.3%</span>.</p> </body></html>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/88565688/image_88565688.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194204-winnebago-slides-after-earnings-reflect-sluggish-retail-demand", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:38:59"}, {"id": "4194155", "title": "NextEra Energy Partners GAAP EPS of -$0.43, revenue of $319M misses by $22.17M", "description": "<html><body><ul> <li>NextEra Energy Partners <a href=\"https://cms.seekingalpha.com/pr/19888531-nextera-energy-third-quarter-2024-financial-results-available-on-companys-website\" rel=\"nofollow\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NEP\" title=\"NextEra Energy Partners, LP Common Units\">NEP</a></span>): Q3 EPS of -$0.43 may not be comparable to $0.56.</li> <li>Revenue of $319M (+3.6% Y/Y) <span style=\"color: red;\"> misses by $22.17M</span>.</li> <li>NextEra Energy Partners continues to expect the run-rate contribution for adjusted EBITDA from itsforecasted portfolio at<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> Dec. 31, 2024, to be in the range of $1.9 billion to $2.1 billion. The year-end 2024run-rate projection reflects expected calendar-year 2025 contributions from the forecasted portfolio atyear-end 2024.</span> </li> </ul> </body></html>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4194155-next-era-energy-partners-gaap-eps-of-0-43-revenue-of-319-m-misses-by-22-17-m", "pub_date": "2024-10-23 15:33:23"}, {"id": "4194156", "title": "PROG Holdings Non-GAAP EPS of $0.77 misses by $0.03, revenue of $606.15M beats by $3.73M", "description": "<html><body><ul> <li>PROG Holdings <a href=\"https://cms.seekingalpha.com/pr/19888535-prog-holdings-reports-third-quarter-2024-results\" rel=\"nofollow\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PRG\" title=\"PROG Holdings, Inc.\">PRG</a></span>): Q3 Non-GAAP EPS of $0.77 <span style=\"color: red;\"> misses by $0.03</span>.</li> <li>Revenue of $606.15M (+4.0% Y/Y) <span style=\"color: green;\"> beats by $3.73M</span>.</li> <li>Progressive Leasing GMV of $456.7 million, 11.6% growth year-over-year</li> <li>FY24 revenue consensus of $2.44B, EPS consensus of $3.38</li> <li><table><tbody> <tr> <td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p> </p></td> <td class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"> </td> <td class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" colspan=\"7\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Revised 2024 Outlook</p></td> <td class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"> </td> <td class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" colspan=\"7\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Previous 2024 Outlook</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> <td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>(In thousands, except per share amounts)</p></td> <td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"> </td> <td colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Low</p></td> <td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"> </td> <td colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>High</p></td> <td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"> </td> <td colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Low</p></td> <td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">